title: Rocket flight and the five dwarfs
summary: Meet the Solar System’s five official dwarf planets, celebrate two major launches, and find out why planets sometimes seem to go backwards across the sky.

title: SpaceX's Starship test flight succeeds despite not reaching orbit

summary: The Planetary Society's all-virtual advocacy event was a success, with more than 1,500 advocacy actions taken.

title: What does “Mercury in retrograde” actually mean?
summary: "Mercury in retrograde" is one of the most searched terms relating to the planet. Astrological interpretations aside, apparent retrograde motion is an interesting phenomenon that has to do with orbital speeds and observer perspective.

title: Meet the Solar System's five official dwarf planets
summary: The International Astronomical Union currently recognizes five dwarf planets: Ceres, Pluto, Haumea, Makemake, and Eris.

title: Want more space? Speak up!
summary: Detailed Mars maps, insights into the Venusian surface, and views of Uranian rings all have one thing in common: they don’t happen without public support for space.

title: Juice launches on mission to explore Jupiter's icy moons
summary: The spacecraft will explore Jupiter's moons Europa, Ganymede, and Callisto, all three of which may harbor subsurface oceans.

title: Digital Day of Action 2023
summary: April 18, 2023, is The Planetary Society's 2023 Digital Day of Action.  Learn how you can get involved and show your support for space exploration.

title: What would it be like to stand on the surface of Venus?
summary: With extreme heat and crushing atmospheric pressure, the surface of Venus is one of the most deadly environments in the Solar System. Here’s what it would be like to be there.

title: ICPS-2: ULA begins readying upper stage for Artemis II launch
